# bench/ publishes the benchmark *method* for OSS transparency — the orchestration
# scripts, the k6 scenarios, the Grafana provisioning, and docker-compose.yml.
#
# It never publishes the raw run artifacts, which carry local paths / machine details
# and are large + regenerable. Keep the following out of git:

# The downloaded third-party k6 binary (run-bench.sh fetches it on demand).
/bin/

# Raw k6 outputs: HTML reports + text logs contain absolute local paths (/home/<user>/…),
# and the JSON summaries are regenerable working data (the curated numbers live in
# performance/). The proxy startup logs echo demo keys + local detail.
/results/
/results-wasm/

# Local results write-up with machine specs; the public report is performance/README.md.
/RESULTS.md

# Belt-and-suspenders: never commit these regardless of where they land under bench/.
*.html
*.log
*.tar.gz
